      <title>Replacing spell lines</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Wizards&amp;message.id=3484#M3484</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;So w/the new expansion coming, we have the potential for change.&amp;nbsp; 1 of the most likely solutions is in spell lines.&amp;nbsp; We have kept the pop system of lures, draughts, big nukes too long.&amp;nbsp; It's time to condense, rearrange, trash, and make new ones.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Like replacing all the banes w/just 1 spell.&amp;nbsp; A chromatic, more overly I think it should be prismatic, -300 nuke.&amp;nbsp; Banes are hardly used, and when they are it usually doesn't matter which you are using.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Sparks well change them all to be like chaos flame, same speed + more efficient&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Extend the claw line, as much as I don't like this spell, it is our sustain.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Not my idea, but w/the current trend of spells have the low-mid dmg spell serve a second purpose. like cov = sustained, cf = quick + mid term length of dps time, magic = stun component.&amp;nbsp; (I'm kinda opposed to this cause at -50 the decision of which type (f/m/c) is still a choice to be made, but w/specialized nukes that limits the decision.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;As for the big nukes, having fire being burst, Ice being the most efficient, and magic being in the middle w/a bonus (a la manaweave) will prolly be the trend (Again I'm kinda of opposed to this, see above~)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;My ideal nuke list would look something like&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Big nuke, big mana cost --&amp;nbsp; EF, however it will need either&amp;nbsp;a significant ratio increase.&amp;nbsp; Being only .5 dmg/mana&amp;nbsp; better than a bane is retarded, I understand it's a gom spell, but when classes can uses thier gom type spell in thier line up&amp;nbsp;just like another spell, I find it unfair. /whine.&amp;nbsp; Or it needs the dmg/mana cost raised so high that you would never want to cast except for gom, but when you did there is no **SMURF**ing way that it didn't go BOOOOM!&amp;nbsp; You know make 30k look like child's play.&amp;nbsp; I like the sooner rather than the latter, however BOOOOM! is always music to my ears.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Fire/Magic/Cold big nukes --&amp;nbsp;All similiar in dps and dpm, nothing fancy just blue collar nukes.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;chromatic/prismatic&amp;nbsp;bane -- read above~&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Fire/Magic/Cold quick cast, mid dmg nukes, specialized -- They all need to be more efficient than the big nukes, faster than than big nukes.&amp;nbsp; Plus each need something special, like stun, have a super dpm ratio, procs (yah move mw proc to something small and more nimble imo) maybe add something besides % dmg&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Stun -- upgrade to telekara&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Rains -- if they're going to be linked, might as well just make it chromatic, not like dmg focus affect them anyways, just more fluff.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
